  10:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/dpath.c ****     MBR & Device Path functions
  11:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/dpath.c **** 
  12:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/dpath.c **** 
  13:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/dpath.c **** 
  14:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/dpath.c **** Revision History
  15:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/dpath.c **** 
  16:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/dpath.c **** 2014/04 B.Burette - updated device path text representation, conforming to
  17:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/dpath.c **** 	UEFI specification 2.4 (dec. 2013). More specifically:
  18:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/dpath.c **** 	- § 9.3.5: added some media types ie. Sata()
  19:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/dpath.c **** 	- § 9.6.1.2: Acpi(PNP0A03,0) makes more sense when displayed as PciRoot(0)
  20:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/dpath.c **** 	- § 9.6.1.5: use commas (instead of '|') between option specific parameters
  21:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/dpath.c **** 	- § 9.6.1.6: hex values in device paths must be preceded by "0x" or "0X"
  22:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/dpath.c **** 
  23:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/dpath.c **** --*/
  24:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/dpath.c **** 
